    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-07T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="710"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/518</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-07T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 8, 6.13 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1052. Referring to the Embassy’s No. 1049, February 5, 11 a.m. [<hi rend="italic"
                        >p.m.</hi>]<note n="1" xml:id="d710fn1">Not printed.</note> French financial
                    delegate Lasteyrie, associate of Mauclère, leaves to-night for Paris, Spanish
                    conferees having declined further to discuss French-Spanish financial agreement
                    pending Department’s final decision concerning our tentative agreement
                    (Embassy’s 1029, January 30, 10 a.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d710fn2">See footnote 1,
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1664">p.
                        1664</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <p>Lasteyrie frankly stated that France is without money or securities and that
                    unless she can obtain credit, she must stop all purchases in Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
